Brazil Prosecutors Recommend Halting Belo Monte Dam Project

-- B y   L u c i a   K a s s a i
-- 
2011-05-27T12:44:13Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-27/brazil-prosecutors-recommend-halting-belo-monte-dam-project.html
Brazilian federal prosecutors
recommend the country’s environmental agency, known as Ibama,
reject a license request to build the Belo Monte dam project in
 Brazil ’s Amazon, according to a  statement  dated yesterday.  The statement is on the Para state’s federal prosecutors’
website.  The 25.8 billion-real ($16 billion) project will flood 516
square kilometers (199 square miles) of forest and has been
criticized by the Organization of the American States, Avatar
director James Cameron and former U.S. President Bill Clinton.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Lucia Kassai in  Sao Paulo  at 
 lkassai@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dale Crofts at 
 dcrofts@bloomberg.net . 